# Environment Variables

This is an example of the environment variables that need to be defined in your .env file.

```
# Application
APP_NAME=YourAppName
APP_ENV=local
APP_KEY=base64:YourBase64Key
APP_DEBUG=true
APP_URL=http://localhost

# Database
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=your_database_name
DB_USERNAME=your_db_username
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password
```
